		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2">
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Sat, Sep 10th 7:54 PM 2005 EST</span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=1;mid=1126366483280704902;num=10;page=1;post=1;replyto=1126396724280999360"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    <a name="1126396724280999360"></a></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=404101"><span class="">intcasta</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />130 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=intcasta;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Warriors get bash, and making a hotkey to bash isn't that hard so you can try to interrupt casters gating or CHing. <br /> <br />For example, <br /> <br /><pre> 
/bandolier activate Bashing 
/doability 4 
/bandolier activate DW 
</pre> <br /> <br />Where Bashing is my bandolier with one hander and shield, my bash is in ability button 4, and DW is my dual wielding set. Keep in mind, this button does not disable when bash timer is refreshing, so I keep my action window open to the abilities tab to watch the 4th button with bash on it. <br /> <br />Another good comment I've heard from warriors on the SOE EQ forums is that they don't want to be given a special bonus which makes wielding a shield full-time a viable alternative where DPS is concerned. It only adds to the different weapons and gear warriors already need to acquire to be effective, now you are introducing a special one hander as well as a shield to my bag with a sword, dagger, stick, big sword, big stick, bow, ranged slot stat item, etc. I'd rather do more LDoNs to get my anger aug than worry about buying a good shield-oriented one hander. <br /> <br />It's easier to address any disparity without adding gear requirements, though I would say that lower melee DPS is not a problem until it actually makes a difference in your ability to hold agro. If you are at that point, you are already doing something wrong. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />This is the end of my post regarding the topic, but since I've already mentioned one of my handy macros I'll also show my pulling one. <br /> <br /><pre> 
/bandolier activate Pulling 
/pause 1,/autofire 
/autofire 
/bandolier activate DW 
</pre> <br /> <br />If you normally carry a bow, you may omit the first and last lines, however I use an item with better stats most of the time so I have my macro set to swap in my Pulling set, which is my one handers with bow/arrow rather than my one handers and ranged slot stat gear. <br /> <br />The line with /pause in it actually executes the pause after the command which follows it on that line. /Pause is the only command that may be seperated from another by a comma as all others need their own line. The parameter is time in 1/10 seconds to wait before moving on in the macro, which allows just enough time to get an arrow off. <br /> <br /> <br />-Posting as my 52 warrior alt,</p>
