<p>Tank class balancing is the topic though. Just cuz your warrior kicks butt in the end game, isn't helping low to mid progressing warrior's get their groups... <br /> <br />I levelled my warrior up to mid 50's before warrior's started having these problems. My friend that complained the most has over 460 AA's now (465 last night, but he was still playing), and he's doing great, still feels a bit enadequate, but I see a great change for the better with him, he's in a Raid guild though. <br /> <br />Warrior's lower in progression are up against things I didn't have to worry about 3 year's ago, so those of you that been around longer, and have been progressing with the expansions, can't possibly know their trouble's unless you have other friends, or have play'd alt warrior's at lower levels that you really tried to progress (Through normal single grouping).&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />All caster class's, including knight's have had their class porgression made alot more progressive.. They have had new spells lines, spells at lower levels, spells at every level of progression, while warrior's recieved mostly stuff that helped the high end. SO yeah, things look good on the top of the hill... <br />In fact even at 68 (Dinged last week), I am starting to have an easier time at things, More AA's, better DPS, aggro is starting to work better for me, I'm actually tanking stuff now with my higher level friends in group's. Things are looking better, and I can see sunlight in the distance. However, the lower Warrior's cannot get AA's they are not of level to get, they cannot get Weapons, and aug's that have level requirements on them, etc. The discs don't even have nothing very good to offer till your within mid 50's, which is also when they get some AA's that might help them out. Before that though, not much of any kind of improvement's, so they have it alot rougher, then for example, what I did 3 year's ago. To say, Well, I been their done that, I can't, cuz it's not the same today as it was then. IF you weren't level 40 last week, you can't possibly know what level 40's are gonna go through next week.  <br /> <br />What's happening to the game in some respects, is level's 1 through level 59 (Probably 69) is getting overlooked, badly, especially when dealing with Warrior's, who only has one job. Don't forget the INcite/berate line of discs, was used as a &quot;temporary&quot; Fix to problems warrior's were facing in POP Expansion. It is now, pretty much permanent. I expect more utility type discs and AA's to even out the playing field, such as the New &quot;Call of Challenge&quot; aa, that will stop a runner and make them turn to fight. The only other thing SOE can do, is make it obviously easier to keep a warrior healed as MT, then A Knight, not just needing one less heal either. I mean NOTICEABLY better tanks. Knight's should be able to tank everything in normal single group content, which other warrior's may not aggree with, but most will aggree that it should be noticeably easier to keep that warrior alive.  <br /> <br />Stun mitigation for Pally's has been parsed to show almost being twice as effective as warrior current ways' of mitigating damage, in normal single group content, for example. What's the bottum line to that mean? A warrior cannot tank &quot;Stunable&quot; content toe to toe, as well as a Pally can is what it means. A warrior will have to have better AC/HP, more defensive AA's, and use disc's to compete, or do it better. Bassically, a Warrior must be alot farther in progression, in thier respective single group makeover. However, they will have to progress more slowly, as most groups will see a greater benefit in getting a higher level warrior for tank, or just use that knight around the same level. So warrior's as was mentioned before, progress slower, doing more trivial content till they do get all the &quot;Goodies&quot; that can be found through AA's, discs, and required level gear.</p>
